# How to Write a Conventional Commit Message
#
# Heres the 72-character limit (* denotes the 72nd character):
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------*
#
# **Subject Line (50 characters max):**
#
# * Start with a verb in the imperative mood (e.g., feat, fix, revert, add, remove).
# * Briefly describe the change (what was done).
# * Capitalize the first letter and don't end with a period.
#
# **Body (optional, wrapped at 72 characters):**
#
# * Provide more details about the change, including the why (rationale behind the change).
# * Mention any relevant issue IDs (e.g., #123).
#
# **Footer (optional):**
#
# * Include "Co-authored-by" lines for contributors.
#   * Format: Co-authored-by: Name <email@focisolutions.com>
#
# **Resources:**
#
# * Conventional Commits: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
#
# **Example:**
#
# feat(api): Add support for new API endpoint (fixes #456)
#
# This commit introduces a new API endpoint for retrieving user data.
#
# Co-authored-by: John Doe <john.doe@focisolutions.com>
#
########################################################################
